{"id":2451,"date":"2017-11-24T13:37:57","date_gmt":"2017-11-24T13:37:57","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=2451"},"modified":"2020-12-15T09:30:25","modified_gmt":"2020-12-15T09:30:25","slug":"import-leads-from-wordpress-contact-form-7","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/import-leads-from-wordpress-contact-form-7\/","title":{"rendered":"Import Leads From WordPress Contact Form 7"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Perfex CRM has the ability to <strong>import\/capture leads<\/strong> from the most popular contact form (and any other customizable forms) for <strong>WordPress Contact Form 7<\/strong> together with the <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/leads-email-integration\/\">Email Integration<\/a> feature which is built in Perfex CRM.<\/p>\n<p>The process is very easy, once you configure the contact form to be compatible with the email integration, you will import leads in no time with the fields filled in contact form automatically added for the imported lead.<\/p>\n<p><strong>We recommend you first to read this whole setup article to get the idea how the contact form fields will be mapped and how the leads will be imported in Perfex CRM to get familiar with the steps you need to perform in order to make this config working, then you can move on to configure the full setup.<\/strong><\/p>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">Prerequisite for this setup is to have previously configured properly working lead email integration in Perfex CRM, click <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/leads-email-integration\/\">here<\/a> to read more how to configure.<\/div>\n<p>For the simplicity of this example and setup, we will use a minimal example for Contact Form config with fields Name, Email, Message<strong>\u00a0(see below for more detailed example).<\/strong><\/p>\n<h4>Install Contact Form 7<\/h4>\n<p><strong>If you already have Contact Form 7 installed and you are familiar with Contact Corm 7 you can skip this step.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>If you haven&#8217;t already installed Contact Form 7, you must install the plugin from your WordPress dashboard area, from the left menu navigate to <strong>Plugins-&gt;Add New<\/strong> and search for <strong>Contact Form 7<\/strong>, after you find the Contact Form 7 plugin click on <strong>Install<\/strong> and after installation click on <strong>Activate<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>We assume that you are already familiar how Contact Form 7 works and how you can embed the form into custom page eq. Contact Us, in case you are not, you can read more by clicking <a href=\"https:\/\/contactform7.com\/docs\/\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n<h4>Configure Contact Form 7<\/h4>\n<p>In this example, we will use the basic Contact Form 7 config which comes with the form after installation.<\/p>\n<p>After you install and activate the plugin from the WordPress admin menu click on <strong>Contact-&gt;Contact Forms<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Chose the form you want to configure and click on the name.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2454 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-e1511517541823.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"721\" height=\"127\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-e1511517541823.png 721w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-e1511517541823-300x53.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-e1511517541823-60x11.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-e1511517541823-150x26.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 721px) 100vw, 721px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Click on the <strong>Mail tab<\/strong> in the contact form to <strong>configure the contact form email to be compatible with Perfex CRM.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-4237 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Opp4MI5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"709\" height=\"768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Opp4MI5.png 709w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Opp4MI5-277x300.png 277w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Opp4MI5-55x60.png 55w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/Opp4MI5-138x150.png 138w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 709px) 100vw, 709px\" \/><\/p>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">It&#8217;s highly recommended always to include the <strong>email<\/strong> field in the message and Reply-To header in the Additional Headers section with the merge fields [your-email]<\/div>\n<p><strong>Additional Hea<\/strong><strong>ders<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Add your Perfex CRM integration email configured in <strong>Setup-&gt;Leads-&gt;Email Integration<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p>In new line add eq.\u00a0<strong>Bcc: yourleadsintegrationemail@example.com<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>Make sure that the Reply-To header is set as shown in the image.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>This is <strong>the important part<\/strong>, in this case when a user fills out the form, the contact form plugin will add BCC your leads email integration email and the Perfex CRM CRON job will be able to catch this email and import the lead with the provided fields.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Message Body<\/strong><\/p>\n<p><strong>The point here is to wrap all form values and include in the email message\/body with:<\/strong><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang:xhtml decode:true\">&lt;div id=\"field_LEAD_FIELD\"&gt;[your-CONTACT-FORM-FIELD]&lt;\/div&gt;<\/pre>\n<p>After the email is sent this field will be populated with the actual field value and will become eq.<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true\">&lt;div id=\"field_LEAD_FIELD\"&gt;John Doe&lt;\/div&gt;<\/pre>\n<p><strong>You will need to replace LEAD_FIELD with the actual <a href=\"#available_lead_fields\">lead field.<\/a><\/strong><\/p>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert- \">You will need actually to create a contact form field in order to add the fields in the email body.<\/div>\n<h4><strong>Use HTML content type<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>In Contact Form 7 mail tab check <strong>Use HTML Content Type<\/strong>, in this case, the email will be HTML.<\/p>\n<h4 id=\"available_lead_fields\"><strong>Available lead fields<\/strong><\/h4>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true\">field_name\nfield_title\nfield_email\nfield_website\nfield_phonenumber\nfield_company\nfield_description\nfield_address\nfield_city\nfield_state\nfield_country\nfield_zip\nfield_lead_value (v2.5.0)<\/pre>\n<h4><strong>Country Field<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>If you are passing a <strong>country field<\/strong>, keep in mind that the country must be ID from Perfex CRM database table for countries (tblcountries) <strong>or<\/strong> the name Eq. United States (without typos) because Perfex CRM script will compare the country name passed in the message body and find suitable country id from Perfex CRM countries table.<\/p>\n<p>Eq user writes United States, this will work fine, but if a user writes a country name that does not exist in countries table or makes a typo eq. <strong>Untited<\/strong> States, Perfex CRM won&#8217;t be able to identify the ID of the country from countries table.<\/p>\n<h4><strong>Custom Fields<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>In case you want to integrate a custom field for a lead, you can use custom_field_<strong>ID,\u00a0<\/strong><strong>Replace the ID<\/strong> with the actual custom field ID which can be found in<strong> Setup-&gt;Custom Fields.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>If you use a custom field the email message markup should look like this:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true \">&lt;div id=\"custom_field_ID\"&gt;[your-CONTACT-FORM-FIELD]&lt;\/div&gt;\n<\/pre>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert- \">Note that if you are adding custom fields of type <strong>Checkbox<\/strong> or <strong>Select<\/strong>, the options must be the same like the one you added in Perfex CRM custom field option in Setup-&gt;Custom Fields. Also for<strong> dates fields<\/strong>, the <strong>dates custom fields must be passed in Y-m-d<\/strong> format.<\/div>\n<p>Eq. example for a custom field of type <strong>Select in Perfex CRM<\/strong> &#8211; Click <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/perfex-crm-custom-field-leads.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a> to see the options config.<\/p>\n<p>Eq. example for a custom field of type <strong>Select in Contact Form 7<\/strong> &#8211; Click <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/perfex-crm-contact-form7-select.png\">here<\/a> to see options config.<\/p>\n<h4><strong>Attachments<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>In the Mail Tab in Contact Form 7 simply <strong>add the field tag<\/strong> <strong>in the File Attachments<\/strong> Area.<\/p>\n<p>Keep in mind that only attachment extensions allowed in Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;General (Perfex CRM installation) will be added while importing the lead.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-2465\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"880\" height=\"124\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments.png 880w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments-300x42.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments-768x108.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments-60x8.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contactform7-file-attachments-150x21.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 880px) 100vw, 880px\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>Full example with more fields<\/h3>\n<p>Let&#8217;s say our Contact Form 7 have fields:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Subject<\/li>\n<li>Name<\/li>\n<li>Email<\/li>\n<li>Website<\/li>\n<li>Phone number<\/li>\n<li>Company<\/li>\n<li>Message<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4><strong>Contact Form Fields<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Our contact form fields config should look like this (<strong>you can format it however you like<\/strong>):<\/p>\n<div class=\"row\"><div class=\"column col-half\"><\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2458 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-fields-e1511526950102.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"402\" height=\"560\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-fields-e1511526950102.png 402w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-fields-e1511526950102-215x300.png 215w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-fields-e1511526950102-43x60.png 43w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-fields-e1511526950102-108x150.png 108w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><\/div><\/p>\n<p><div class=\"column col-half\"><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true\">&lt;label&gt; Subject\n    [text* your-subject] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Your Name (required)\n    [text* your-name] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Your Email (required)\n    [email* your-email] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Website\n    [text your-website] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Phone Number\n    [text your-phonenumber] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Company\n    [text your-company] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n&lt;label&gt; Your Message\n    [textarea your-message] &lt;\/label&gt;\n\n[submit \"Send\"]<\/pre>\n<p><\/div><\/p>\n<p><\/div>\n<h4>Mail Tab Config<\/h4>\n<p>Click on the mail tab to configure the email body content.<\/p>\n<p>You can get the available shortcodes of the field values at the top of the Mail Tab Config where it says <strong>&#8220;In the following fields, you can use these mail-tags&#8221;<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>The email body content should look like this:<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-1024x319.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-large wp-image-2459\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-1024x319.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"980\" height=\"305\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-1024x319.png 1024w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-300x93.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-768x239.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-60x19.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config-150x47.png 150w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/contact-form-7-perfex-email-tempalte-config.png 1379w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 980px) 100vw, 980px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang:default decode:true\">From: [your-name] &lt;[your-email]&gt;\nSubject: [your-subject]\n\nName:\n&lt;div id=\"field_name\"&gt;[your-name]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\nEmail:\n&lt;div id=\"field_email\"&gt;[your-email]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\nWebsite:\n&lt;div id=\"field_website\"&gt;[your-website]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\nPhone Number:\n&lt;div id=\"field_phonenumber\"&gt;[your-phonenumber]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\nCompany:\n&lt;div id=\"field_company\"&gt;[your-company]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\nMessage Body:\n&lt;div id=\"field_description\"&gt;[your-message]&lt;\/div&gt;\n\n-- \nThis e-mail was sent from a contact form on Perfex CRM (https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com)<\/pre>\n<p>You can see how <strong>all field values are wrapped within div with id=&#8221;field_LEAD_FIELD&#8221;<\/strong>, the <strong>LEAD_FIELD<\/strong> is actually from the <a href=\"#available_lead_fields\">available lead fields<\/a><\/p>\n<p><strong>In this example the message that the user will write in the contact form we are populating the lead description text area, which is suitable for this case.<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Keep in mind that <strong>the subject won&#8217;t be added to the leads section<\/strong> of Perfex CRM because the subject is not suitable for any field that belongs to lead, you can either create a custom field or you will be able to view the subject by clicking on the <strong>Email Activity tab<\/strong> in the lead modal, click <a href=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/11\/perfex-crm-leads-email-integration-subject.png\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here<\/a> to check how this will look.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<p>Now when a user fills Contact Form 7 the plugin will add your email integration email as BCC header and this email will be sent too to the email integration email.<\/p>\n<p>The Perfex CRM cron job will read this email and map all fields provided within the email message and import the lead in Perfex CRM leads section.<\/p>\n<hr \/>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-success \">You can apply this logic to any WordPress contact\/form plugin which allows you to change the email content and add BCC, you can even use this with a pure PHP email form, you just need to BCC your leads email integration and format the email body as mentioned above, isn&#8217;t this awesome?<\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Perfex CRM has the ability to import\/capture leads from the most popular contact form (and any other customizable forms) for WordPress Contact Form 7 together with the Email Integration feature which is built in Perfex CRM. The process is very easy, once you configure the contact form to be compatible with the email integration, you [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":2476,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[31,14],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-2451","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-setup-and-configuration","category-leads"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2451","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=2451"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/2451\/revisions"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2476"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2451"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2451"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=2451"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}